<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-intervals-c-harmonic-minor-ascending" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Example of intervals, with count and notation in an ascending C Melodic Minor scale</title>

  <p>In the Melodic Minor Scale the sixth and seventh notes of the Natural Minor scale are raised by a half step when ascending and the descending scale is as the Natural Minor scale.</p>

  <figure xml:id="fig-intervals-c-harmonic-minor-ascending-table">
    <caption>Examples of intervals with notation and semitone counts (ascending C melodic minor).</caption>
    <image>
      <latex-image>
        <![CDATA[
\newcommand{\MusiC}[1]{\adjustbox{trim=145pt 0pt 140pt 0pt, valign=c}{%
  \begin{music}
    \nobarnumbers
    \setclef10
    \startextract
    \notes #1
    \endextract
  \end{music}}}

\begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|c|c|c|}
  \hline
  Interval & Quality & Notes & On Staff & Number of Semitones & Count\\
  \hline
  Second & Major     & C~-~D          & \MusiC{\qa c \qa d \en} & 2 & 3\\
  \hline
  Second & Minor     & D~-~E flat     & \MusiC{\qa d \qa {_e} \en} & 1 & 2\\
  \hline
  Second & Major     & E flat~-~F     & \MusiC{\qa {_e} \qa f \en} & 2 & 3\\
  \hline
  Second & Major     & F~-~G          & \MusiC{\qa f \qa g \en} & 2 & 3\\
  \hline
  Second & Major     & G~-~A            & \MusiC{\qa g \qa h \en} & 2 & 3\\
  \hline
  Second & Major     & A~-~B     & \MusiC{\qa h \qa i \en} & 2 & 3\\
  \hline
  Second & Minor     & B~-~C          & \MusiC{\qa i \qa j \en} & 1 & 2\\
  \hline
\end{tabular}
        ]]>
      </latex-image>
    </image>
  </figure>

</section>
